<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Apiosporaceae" genus="Arthrinium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Arthrinium guizhouense" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="guizhouense">Arthrinium guizhouense</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. sacchari" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species" species="sacchari">A. sacchari</taxonomicName>
(Speg.) M.B. Ellis (99% sequence similarity in ITS; 99% in TUB2; 94% in TEF1). Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. guizhouense" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species" species="guizhouense">A. guizhouense</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. sacchari" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species" species="sacchari">A. sacchari</taxonomicName>
are very similar in conidial size, but 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. guizhouensis" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species" species="guizhouensis">A. guizhouensis</taxonomicName>
produces relatively shorter conidiogenous cells (3.5-8.0 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. guizhouense" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species" species="guizhouense">A. guizhouense</taxonomicName>
vs. 5-12 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. sacchari" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species" species="sacchari">A. sacchari</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
